# Core philosophy

- Naming for functions and methods lives in `.cursor/rules/functions.mdc`.
- TypeScript declaration naming lives in `.cursor/rules/typescript.mdc`.

## Fix the root cause, not the symptom

- Trace failures to the source (wrong assumption, missing invariant, bad data shape, lifecycle bug) and change that layer.
- Avoid patching only the visible error.

## Prefer existing patterns before new abstractions

- Search the codebase for similar flows before implementing new solutions (routing, data loading, styling, error handling).
- Extend or mirror existing patterns instead of introducing a parallel approach.

## Functional style over object-oriented

- Prefer pure functions, narrow inputs/outputs, and composition.

## Follow the codebase conventions

- Add JSDoc per `.cursor/rules/jsdocs.mdc` for exported functions, hooks, components, and non-obvious types/interfaces.
- Follow Tailwind conventions — `.cursor/rules/tailwind.mdc`.
- Follow TypeScript conventions — `.cursor/rules/typescript.mdc`.
- Follow function naming — `.cursor/rules/functions.mdc`.
- One exported function per file (including small helpers) — `.cursor/rules/module.mdc`.
